Description:
First Home Buyers, Families & Investors This Is The One!
Conveniently set within walking distance to local amenities, this property presents a terrific opportunity for first homebuyers, investors, and families alike!
Young families will appreciate that Geelong East Primary School and the Breakwater Pre-School Centre are within easy walking distance from the front door. The Gordon Tafe East Geelong Campus is also a short stroll away, along with public transport and the sporting grounds of St Albans Reserve. With Buckleys Entertainment Centre just up the road, family nights out will be a breeze. Enjoy close access to the Bellarine Highway shopping centres and the Geelong Racecourse.
The original interiors grant you the option to move straight in or to refresh with your own personal touch (STCA). The lounge overlooks the spacious front yard and flows through to the dining/kitchen area. The kitchen is equipped with a built-in pantry and cooking appliances (oven, gas hob, rangehood).
Three bedrooms (one with built-in robes) share close access to the main bathroom, which is complete with a shower, single vanity, and toilet. The study nook, laundry, and 2nd toilet complete the internal layout. Youll be comfortable in all seasons thanks to a gas wall heater, split-system air conditioner, and ceiling fan.
Outside, the large sheltered deck flows onto the north-facing backyard putting the foundations in place for great outdoor living! The backyard is home to a herb garden, storage shed, and bungalow. Bursting with potential, the bungalow offers versatility as a kids play space, teen retreat, workshop, or studio.
The long driveway features an oversized single carport, along with access to the backyard making this an ideal choice for those needing to store caravans, boats, or trailers.
If youre searching for easy and convenient living, then this home is the one for you! Inspect ASAP!

Address: 92 Homestead Drive St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
Uncompromised family home.
On offer here, in the blue-chip suburb of St Albans Park is this feature-packed family home with a lot to offer. This family-oriented residence offers 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, in-ground swimming pool, garaging for 3 cars and off-street parking for a boat or caravan. Ideally suited to those searching for a first home, investment, or those that need extra garage space/storage.
On entry, the wide hallway provides a welcoming entrance and opens into the light-filled front lounge. Across the hall way is a 4th bedroom, which could easily be utilised as a home office if desired. The open-plan living and dining area is centrally located and opens through glass sliding doors to the beautiful north facing alfresco. The updated kitchen features Stainless steel appliances including 600mm oven and gas cook top and a double drawer dishwasher. The kitchen also overlooks the alfresco and backyard, perfect for keeping an eye on the kids in the self-chlorinated and solar heated in-ground swimming pool.
Accommodation consists of a sizable master suite with ceiling fan, walk in robe and ensuite; and 2 further bedrooms with built in robes and ceiling fans, serviced by a central bathroom with shower, bath and separate toilet.
Secure and private, the backyard is perfect for those with pets and children and offers a 1.5 car garage/workshop with adjoining garden shed and drive through access from the remote double garage. Further off street parking is available to the other side of the home, which could easily be adapted to store a car or trailer behind closed gates.
Notable features include:
- Split system air conditioning.
- Gas ducted heating.
- 8 panel solar system.
- Rear roller door access from garage.
- Ceiling fans in all bedrooms.
Positioned within walking distance to local reserves, public transport, walking/bike tracks, and only a short drive to everyday amenities, this location is certainly convenient. Enquire today!

Description:
BRIGHT TOWNHOUSE ON THE BORDER OF EAST GEELONG
This bright 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom spacious townhouse is only 1 of 3 and is set in a quiet pocket of Thomson and would suit a FHB, savvy investor with an approx. rent of $340 pw or downsizer with a neat garden to potter in.
Comprising of two spacious bedrooms, both with BIR, modern venetian blinds and one bedroom with reverse cycle Fujitsu split system.
The bright central bathroom offers sunken bath, separate shower and heat lamps for those chilly mornings. There is also a separate toilet.
The roomy functional laundry offers built in storage cupboard and trough.
Located at the rear of the home is a wonderfully bright open plan kitchen/dining and spacious living area.
The kitchen is equipped with 4 burner gas cooking, Miele dishwasher, ample cupboard space and breakfast bar seating up to 3. The dining area easily sits 6+ and flows beautifully off the kitchen and offers a garden outlook.
The bright carpeted living area has multiple large windows and comes equipped with a second Fujitsu split system for all year round comfort.
Outside you will find an L shaped rear yard, lush established gardens and quality high fencing. This wonderful neat townhouse is located on the border of East Geelong and Thomson and is less than 2km from Geelong CBD, close to local train station, walking distance to Newcomb Shopping Centre and 20 mins to the coast.

The naturally light filled open plan living, dining and kitchen area conveys a feeling of space and comfort and is ideal for the keen home entertainer with an island bench with plenty of storage and bench space and stainless steel appliances including gas cook top, electric oven, range hood and dishwasher. All of this is just minutes from local shops, schools and public transport and with all that Geelong and the Bellarine has to offer right on your door step its no wonder why this location is so hot right now. Make the time to inspect and prepare to be delighted!

open light filled living/dining area adjoining the spacious kitchen with stainless appliances
large built in sun-room or 3rd living area on the north side featuring a wood heater and tv point for watching the footy or entertaining on those cold winter nights
separate basin and vanity area outside the main bathroom (perfect for accommodating family members who like spending lots of time in front of the mirror without tying up the bathroom)
generous master bedroom with bay window, ensuite and walk in robe
covered BBQ area behind the garage with rear roller-door to the garage giving access through to the yard
huge 684m2 block with expansive sheltered, manicured flat lawn area at the back, perfect for family games or pets that need room to roam
central gas heating and split system cooling/heating
This intelligently designed and immaculate home is ready for the fussy buyer, there is not a cent to be spent and you will love coming home to this delightful warm property. Phone Kardinia Property now for an inspection.

Description:
SOLID START ON THE FRINGE OF EAST GEELONG
Situated on the fringe of East Geelong this well loved and meticulously maintained brick veneer 3 bed, 1 bath, solid home set on 675m2 approx is the perfect choice for first home buyers, and investors alike with a potential rent of approx $360 pw .
Stepping foot into this property you will find a comfortable front living room equipped with ornate gas heater and ceiling fan for all year round comfort.
The master bedroom is located at the front of the home and is large in size and offers BIR and ceiling fan. Down the hall you will find an additional 2 good sized bedrooms.
Located at the rear of the home is a spacious updated kitchen and meals area, equipped with modern tiled flooring, 4 burner gas cooktop and AEG oven, plus ample cupboard space all in a neutral colour palette. The meals area easily seats up to 4+ and makes for a great space for everyone to come together.
Adjacent to the kitchen you will find an updated central bathroom, neatly renovated and offering corner shower, vanity storage and skylight.
What sets this home apart from the rest is the second living/enclosed sunroom, neatly renovated with a beautiful back yard view. This multipurpose space would make for an ideal study, sitting room or second summer living.
Stepping outside onto the merbau deck and undercover pergola, which is perfect for summer BBQ's and outdoor entertaining.
The spacious rear grassed yard and well pruned gardens are low maintenance would suit kids or your four legged friend. There is also a 1.5 SLUG garage and workshop ideal to tinker in.
This wonderful property is conveniently located less then 2km from Geelong CBD, walking distance to Botanical Gardens and Eastern Beach and close to Newcomb Shopping Centre.
FEATURES
-675 m2 block approx
-Gas Heating
-Carrier Split system Heat/Cool
-Rent pw $360 approx
-2 living rooms

Description:
Enviable Family Entertainer - Blending Comfort & Convenience!
Home Owner Comment "We love that our home was built with love and that there is so much room for the kids to play
Perfectly nestled in a quiet court of St Albans Park is this brick veneer family home that offers comfort throughout, while situated on a substantial 774m2 allotment.
Designed with the family and entertaining in mind, the residence gracefully supports multiple living zones, incorporating two family friendly separate living spaces. Stepping into the kitchen, the heart of the home will stimulate family unity with its open plan dining, flowing through to the living zone / rumpus room. The kitchen is complete with dishwasher, gas cooking, breakfast bar and ample cupboards to accommodate families big and small.
Entirely zoned, this home consists of three large bedrooms all with built in robes, master with full ensuite and walk in robe.
If entertaining is your specialty, then the undercover outdoor entertaining area is sure to be one of the many aspects that attracts you to this property. In the private rear yard, enjoy many relaxing days in the alfresco area that is both grand in scale & functionality. Surrounded by a manicured backyard coupled with ample space for the young ones, you will feel right at home from the moment you move in and put your feet up to revel in all that this home has to offer.
The home is additionally lavished with ducted heating, reverse cycle heating and cooling, solar panels, water tank, high ceilings that complement the natural light that flows beautifully throughout the property.
If car accommodation is a priority than this one will tick the boxes; with the two-car garage and drive through access to the rear yard; ideal storage for a boat or caravan, plus additional double garage at the rear of the property.
Just 15 minutes drive to the Surf Coast in one direction and a short drive to Geelongs CBD in the other. This growth corridor of Geelong is further serviced by local shopping centres, parks, childcare centres and bus stops within walking distance, schools and recreational facilities make for a lifestyle of true convenience. This home will make life too convenient for you to go past- an inspection will impress!
Roncon Real Estate An Agency like no other!

Description:
Modern Living On Myers
This stylish, simple and a spacious townhouse ticks all the boxes, a beautifully designed home that has everything you desire. Situated in the heart of East Geelong, this home boasts low maintenance gardens, excellent entertaining qualities and light filled rooms which can lap up the sun all year round.
On offer are 3 spacious bedrooms, master with full size ensuite and walk in robe, second and third bedrooms are both generous in size and have built in robes, large central bathroom with full size bath and ample lighting, modern and newly renovated kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances, beautiful floorboards. The sun filled, North facing living area is warm and welcoming, taking advantage of the northern sunshine, additional formal living room, laundry and ample storage throughout the home.
Stepping outside we have a North facing backyard perfect for relaxing or entertaining, DLUG with extra width, keyless entry and rear-lane access.
Perfectly ideal for the downsizer, small family, or investment, you too could live an easy distance to East Geelong's Boutique Cafe Precinct, local Schools, public transport, botanic gardens, Geelong Waterfront and the CBD. This property won't last long!
